{
  "text": "For diversity to be meaningful, these complexities need to be captured and reflected in policy and public discourse, and the systems that incentivise and reward institutions and individuals. However, there is little doubt that diversity breeds complexity -and potentially undermines another government objective of cost containment and efficiency. To be fair to both the goal and the process, a multi-faceted process that meets the different objectives needs to be developed. One solution is to change the assessment and reward system, for institutions and individuals, to better align it with policy intentions rather than \"systems that distort academic investments and produce inequality \u2026\" [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
